question
Write a function with isNegativeInArray that takes an array arr as a name argument and returns true if the array has at least 
one negative element and false otherwise. You must use the break statement in your solution.
Indication. Set some model to false. Loop through the array, and if a negative element is encountered, set this to true and the loop ends.
Examples:
the isNegativeInArray ([1, 2, 3, 9, 0]) function must return false;
the isNegativeInArray ([2, 1, -3, 4, 3]) function must return true;
the isNegativeInArray ([2, 1, -3, -4, 3]) function must return true.

solution:

function isNegativeInArray(arr){
 let answer = false;
  for (let el of arr) {
    if (el < 0) {
      answer = true;
      break;
    }
  }
  return answer;
}
